 PROJECT 1 (Day 1–3)
js-menu-system → Pure JavaScript Brain Training
 Folder Setup
js-menu-system/
 ├── index.html
 ├── style.css  
 └── app.js

A fully dynamic restaurant menu using ONLY Vanilla JS.
Data (Hardcode in app.js)
Create array:

const foods = [
 { id:1, name:"Paneer Tikka", category:"veg", price:250 },
 { id:2, name:"Chicken Curry", category:"nonveg", price:320 },
 ...
]

Add at least 15 items.
 Features To Implement
1️Render Items Dynamically
Nothing written in HTML.
JS must create cards using createElement.
2️ Category Filter Buttons
Buttons:
All | Veg | Non-Veg | Drinks
Click → filter array → re-render.
3️Search Bar
Typing should instantly filter by name.
4️Sort Dropdown
Price Low → High
Price High → Low
5️ Empty State
If nothing matches → show:
"No Items Found"
Skills This Builds
DOM control
Data → UI mapping
Real filtering logic
Re-render mindset (important for React)


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 PROJECT 2 (Day 4–5)
js-menu-async-cart → Async + State Simulation
Copy previous project → extend it.
 Now You Simulate Backend Behavior
1️ Fake API Call
Wrap data in:
function fetchFoods(){
 return new Promise(resolve=>{
   setTimeout(()=> resolve(foods), 1000)
 })
}
Show:
Loading menu...
before render.
2️ Add To Cart System (LocalStorage)
Each card gets Add to Cart button.
Store cart:
localStorage.setItem("cart", JSON.stringify(cart))
3️ Cart Counter in Navbar
Must update live when items added.
4️ Error Simulation Button
Create button:
"Simulate Server Error"
Show error UI + Retry option.
 Skills This Builds
Async thinking
UI states (loading/error/success)
Persistence
App lifecycle understanding

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



 PROJECT 3 (Day 6–7)
react-menu-rebuild → Convert Same Logic to React
 Component Structure
src/
 ├── components/
 │    ├── Menu.jsx
 │    ├── Filters.jsx
 │    ├── FoodCard.jsx
 │    └── Navbar.jsx
 └── App.jsx
 Features (Same as JS Version)
But now using:
useState
useEffect
props
derived filtering
No Context. No Redux.
 Skills This Builds
Understanding:
React is just re-rendering JS logic.
